                  <history>
                    <origin>
                      <origDate when="1899">
                        According to <ref target="#colophon1"/>, the manuscript was written in the year of mercy 
                        <date calendar="ethiopian" when-custom="1891" notBefore="1898" notAfter="1899">1891 EC</date>, during the reign
                        of <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> and the episcopacy of <persName ref="PRS6876Matewos"/>.
                        According to the catalogue, the manuscript was produced for the use of young students.
                      </origDate>
                    </origin>
                    <provenance>According to the account on the manuscripts’ provenance given by Eugène Tisserant, this manuscript is among those
                      acquired by <persName ref="PRS4805Grebaut" role="owner"/> in <date when="1925"/> with funds of
                      <persName ref="PRS14055SaintJ">Jean Saint</persName>. 
                      The manuscripts originated from Šawā (ʾAddis ʾAbabā, Dabra Libānos, Dabra Bǝrhān),
                      Goǧǧām (Dimā Giyorgis, Marṭula Māryām, Dabra Warq) and Bagemdǝr (Gondar, ʾAzazo Takla Hāymānot), and very few from Tǝgrāy.
                    </provenance>
                    <acquisition when="1928">The manuscript entered the library on <date when="1928-04-18">18 April 1928</date>.</acquisition>
